          "title": "CPP004: Cardiac Arrest \u2013 Adult",
          "category": "Cardiac",
          "scope": "PTO",
          "background": "Any patient unconscious and not breathing normally should be presumed in cardiac arrest. Pulse palpation unreliable \u2014 if doubt, commence compressions. High-quality CPR and early defibrillation are the cornerstone of resuscitation.",
