            "What SpO2 defines critical respiratory status?",
            "A patient can only speak in words \u2014 what RSA grade is this?"
          ],
          "assessment_table": {"type":"rsa","description":"RSA grades respiratory distress across 9 parameters","parameters":["General Appearance","Speech","Breath Sounds","Respiratory Rate","Respiratory Rhythm","Work of Breathing","Heart Rate","Skin","Conscious State"],"grades":[{"grade":"No Distress","appearance":"Calm or quiet","speech":"Clear, steady sentences","sounds":"Bronchospasm: quiet, no wheeze. Oedema: no crackles or scattered fine crackles","rr":"12–16","rhythm":"Regular, even cycles","work":"Normal chest movement","hr":"60–100","skin":"Normal","conscious_state":"Alert"},{"grade":"Mild Distress","appearance":"Mildly anxious","speech":"Full sentences","sounds":"Bronchospasm: mild expiratory wheeze. Oedema: crackles at base","rr":"16–20","rhythm":"Slight increase in normal chest movement","work":"Slight increase in normal effort","hr":"60–100","skin":"Normal","conscious_state":"Alert"},{"grade":"Moderate Distress","appearance":"Distressed or anxious","speech":"Short phrases","sounds":"Bronchospasm: expiratory wheeze +/- inspiratory wheeze. Oedema: crackles base to mid-zone","rr":">20","rhythm":"Bronchospasm: prolonged expiratory phase. Oedema: short sharp breaths","work":"Marked chest movement +/- accessory muscles","hr":"100–120","skin":"Pale and sweaty","conscious_state":"May be altered"},{"grade":"Severe Distress","appearance":"Distressed, anxious","speech":"Words only","sounds":"Bronchospasm: expiratory and inspiratory wheeze. Oedema: full-field crackles +/- wheeze","rr":">20","rhythm":"Bronchospasm: prolonged expiratory phase. Oedema: short sharp breaths","work":"Marked chest movement with accessory muscles, intercostal retraction +/- tracheal tugging","hr":">120","skin":"Pale and sweaty +/- cyanosis","conscious_state":"Altered"},{"grade":"Critical","appearance":"Fighting to breathe, or catatonic","speech":"Unable to speak, single word or grunting","sounds":"Bronchospasm: little to no air movement — silent chest. Oedema: full field crackles +/- wheeze OR little to no air movement","rr":">30 or <8","rhythm":"Bronchospasm: prolonged expiratory phase. Oedema: short sharp breaths","work":"Marked chest movement, accessory muscles, intercostal retraction +/- tracheal tugging OR reduced effort due to fatigue","hr":">120 or bradycardic (late stage)","skin":"Pale, sweaty, peripheral cyanosis, may be central cyanosis (late sign)","conscious_state":"Altered or catatonic (no purposeful movements)"}]}
