          "title": "CPP004: Cardiac Arrest \u2013 Adult",
          "category": "Cardiac",
          "scope": "RNCC",
          "background": "Any patient unconscious and not breathing normally should be presumed in cardiac arrest. Pulse palpation unreliable \u2014 if doubt, commence compressions. High-quality CPR and early defibrillation are the cornerstone of resuscitation.",
          "recognition": [
            "Unconscious, not breathing normally (e.g. gasping, agonal breathing) and pulseless \u2014 or unsure of pulse",
            "If traumatic cause is suspected refer to CPP002: Clinical Approach to Assessment \u2013 Unplanned Major Trauma. Control major haemorrhage as a priority."
          ],
          "memory_items": [
            "Commence CPR immediately",
            "Apply defibrillation pads early",
            "Escalate per CPP006 as early as practicable",
            "CPR rate: 100\u2013120/min | Depth: \u22655cm | Full recoil",
            "No SGA: 30:2 ratio, pause for ventilations",
            "SGA/ETT: 15:1 ratio, 6\u20138 breaths/min, no pause",
            "Defibrillate at 2-minute intervals: Apex L mid-axillary 6th ICS, Sternal R upper chest"
          ],
          "checklist_steps": [
